OL,3,CThousands gather at Stonehenge to mark
OL,4,Csummer solstice
OL,6,FOn the summer solstice, the sun rises
OL,7,Fbehind the Heel Stone -the ancient
OL,8,Fentrance to the Stone Circle ` and
OL,9,Frays of sunlight are channelled into
OL,10,Fthe centre of the monument.
OL,12,FIt is believed solstices have been
OL,13,Fcelebrated at Stonehenge for thousands
OL,14,Fof years.
OL,16,FThe summer solstice takes place as one
OL,17,Fof the Earth's poles has its maximum
OL,18,Ftilt toward the sun as it reaches its
OL,19,Fhighest position in the sky, ensuring
OL,20,Fthe longest period of daylight for the
OL,21,Fyear.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
